Class Database

java.lang.Object
iutforces_server.Database
public class Database

    • addProblemToDB

      public boolean addProblemToDB​(newproblem.NewProblem problem, java.lang.String username)
      This function adds a new problem to the database. The problem ID is determined by figuring out the ProblemID with the maximum value. The next problem which is added has an ID which is 1 more than the max ID.
      Parameters:
      problem - The object of NewProblem class.
      username - The username of the problem's author.
      Returns:
      success/failure Returns true if adding was successful and false if adding resulted in failure.

    • deleteProblem

    • getProblemTable

      public java.lang.String[][] getProblemTable​(java.lang.String identifier, java.lang.String identifier2)
      This function returns a 2D String array which is the table of problems displayed in the following tabs: Problems (User + Admin), My Problems (Delete Problem, only Admin).
      Parameters:
      identifier - Identifier string to identify which format of the Problem table has to be generated. ("null" for Problems tab listing out all the problems)
      identifier2 - Identifier string to identify which format of the Problem table has to be generated. ("MyDel" for the My Problem tab's Delete Problem sub-tab)
      Returns:
      The two-dimensional String array containing the Problems Table.

    • getStatusTable

      public java.lang.String[][] getStatusTable​(java.lang.String identifier)
      This function returns a 2D String array which is the table of submissions displayed in the following tabs: Status (User + Admin), My Submissions (only User).
      Parameters:
      identifier - Identifier string to identify which format of the Status table has to be generated. ("nullad" for Admin's Status Table, "nullus" for User's Status Table, otherwise the User's own Status table in My Submissions tab)
      Returns:
      The two-dimensional String array containing the Status Table.

    • getStandingsTable

      public java.lang.String[][] getStandingsTable​(java.lang.String identifier)
      This function returns a 2D String array which is the Standings Table displayed in the following tab: Standings (User + Admin).
      Parameters:
      identifier - (not necessary) Identifier string to identify which format of the Standings table has to be generated.
      Returns:
      The two-dimensional String array containing the Standings Table.
